Req. ID: 291303 
As a Product Yield Enhancement (PYE) Physical Failure Analysis (PFA) Engineering Technician for Micron Technology, Inc., you will be responsible for providing full physical failure analysis, circuit edits and functional de-capsulation, supporting qualifications, customer returns, new device introduction, and general test failures. You will become an authority on physical failure analysis, circuit edits and de-capsulation methods, tools, and techniques. You will also be responsible for understanding all relevant analytical techniques; electrical failure modes, architecture, fabrication process, device operation and device physics for solid state memory devices. In this work environment you will be required to follow lab policies and safety procedures. 
Responsibilities include, but not limited to: 
Conducting Physical Defect Analysis 
Performing Circuit Edit 
Conducting Functional De-Capsulation 
Qualifications: 
A positive attitude and high level of motivation 
The ability to work at a fast pace without compromising quality 
Be a team player 
Effective time and project management skills 
Effective communication skills 
Problem solving and critical thinking skills 
Effective customer relationship building skills 
Scanning Electron Microscope (SEM) 
Focused Ion Beam (FIB) 
Sample preparation (etching and mechanical polishing) 
Cadence (CAD) 
Electronics and basic understanding of failure mechanisms 
Analytical techniques such as EDS 
Basic understanding of semiconductor fabrication and assembly processes 
The ability to work a 12 hour shift, rotating Day/Night shifts, every 4 months. Actual days TBD 
Education: 
B.S. in a non-engineering field of study (e.g. Biology, Chemistry, Geology, Phyics) 
A.A.S in Electronics, Microscopy or combination of education and applicable experience. 
